WEBVTT

00:37.338 --> 00:40.208
** [ Bossa Nova ]

01:06.900 --> 01:08.802
** [ Ends ]

01:11.405 --> 01:13.741
** [ Bossa Nova ]

01:19.547 --> 01:22.616
[ Narrator ]
Once upon a time,
in the land of bossa nova,

01:22.716 --> 01:25.186
lived a girl
named Isabella.

01:25.286 --> 01:30.057
When she was born,
the gods blessed her
with extraordinary beauty.

01:30.158 --> 01:33.060
But overlooked
one itty-bitty flaw--

01:33.161 --> 01:35.229
motion sickness.

01:36.230 --> 01:38.299
Her parents
tried everything:

01:38.399 --> 01:40.434
conventional medicine,

01:40.534 --> 01:42.436
organized religion,

01:42.536 --> 01:45.373
alternative religion.

01:45.473 --> 01:48.209
Nothing worked...

01:48.309 --> 01:50.844
until Yemanja,
[ Thunderclap ]

01:50.944 --> 01:52.846
goddess of the sea,

01:52.946 --> 01:56.517
took pity on the child
and compensated her with a
gift.

01:59.853 --> 02:02.523
Too frail to play
with her friends,

02:02.623 --> 02:05.693
Isabella spent her days
in the kitchen
with the family cook.

02:11.599 --> 02:14.235
She blossomed into a shy
but dazzling girl,

02:14.335 --> 02:18.206
who could melt the palates
and the hearts of men.

02:19.740 --> 02:21.575
Isabella dreamed
of traveling the world

02:21.675 --> 02:23.577
and becoming a famous chef.

02:23.677 --> 02:27.848
** [ Man Vocalizing ]

02:27.948 --> 02:30.851
But when she laid eyes
on the dashing Toninho,

02:30.951 --> 02:34.655
all of her dreams
took flight.

02:34.755 --> 02:37.625
** [ Bossa Nova Continues ]

02:43.631 --> 02:46.900
It was love...
at first bite.

02:47.000 --> 02:49.403
** [ Singing In Portuguese ]

02:59.613 --> 03:04.318
They fell so madly in love
that they knew nothing
could ever keep them apart.

03:05.586 --> 03:07.921
[ Cheering ]
** [ Singing Continues ]

03:15.529 --> 03:17.465
[ Sobbing ]

03:24.572 --> 03:26.874
[ Narrator ]
With Isabella's exotic dishes,

03:26.974 --> 03:30.444
Toninho's new restaurant
was the hottest spot in Brazil.

03:30.544 --> 03:33.847
** [ Bossa Nova ]
She did all the work.

03:33.947 --> 03:37.618
[ Chatter In Portuguese ]
He got all the credit.

03:44.358 --> 03:48.362
And though she got job offers
from all over the planet,

03:48.462 --> 03:52.232
Isabella's dreams
of worldwide glory
would melt away...

03:52.333 --> 03:55.436
in Toninho's
irresistible embrace.

04:20.461 --> 04:23.497
Now, Isabella could control
her motion sickness...

04:23.597 --> 04:25.999
only by controlling
her motions.

04:27.668 --> 04:31.405
- If she always drove...
- [ Portuguese ]

04:33.874 --> 04:36.276
if she always led...

04:36.377 --> 04:39.913
** [ Man Singing
In Portuguese ]

04:40.013 --> 04:43.484
[ All Laughing ]

04:44.785 --> 04:47.788
if she always stayed
on top...

04:47.888 --> 04:49.890
everything was just fine.

05:05.506 --> 05:09.977
Ah, but some men
must always appear to be men,

05:11.044 --> 05:13.547
no matter
what it may cost.

05:23.791 --> 05:25.859
[ Gasps ]

05:27.895 --> 05:29.797
Isabella!

05:29.897 --> 05:32.700
Isabella!
I'm a man.

05:32.800 --> 05:35.068
I have to be on top
sometimes.

05:40.774 --> 05:42.843
Give me the strength,
Yemanja.

05:42.943 --> 05:45.946
Please give me the strength
to leave him...

05:46.046 --> 05:48.416
and Bahia.

05:48.516 --> 05:50.584
[ Thunderclap ]

05:50.684 --> 05:52.686
[ Glass Breaks ]

05:55.923 --> 05:58.626
[ Narrator ]
Her prayers were answered.

06:00.428 --> 06:03.997
And thus begins
our story of love,

06:04.097 --> 06:08.368
motion sickness
and the art of cooking.

06:08.469 --> 06:10.370
[ Narrator Chuckles ]

06:14.141 --> 06:16.043
[ Toninho ]
Isabella!

06:22.716 --> 06:24.652
[ Toninho ]
Isabella!

06:26.119 --> 06:28.055
Isabella!

06:35.796 --> 06:40.634
[ Woman On P.A. ]
Varig announces the arrival
of flight number 732.

06:40.734 --> 06:42.836
[ Continues, Indistinct ]

06:47.808 --> 06:50.377
** [ Man Singing
In Portuguese ]

06:50.478 --> 06:52.379
[ Tires Skid ]

06:52.480 --> 06:54.381
Please, I beg you.

06:54.482 --> 06:56.416
There is no way
I'm gonna do that.

07:04.224 --> 07:06.927
** [ Woman Singing
In Portuguese ]

07:16.136 --> 07:18.939
[ Truck Horn Honks ]

07:23.143 --> 07:25.779
[ Tires Skidding ]

07:25.879 --> 07:27.715
[ Horn Honks ]

07:31.619 --> 07:33.987
[ Trolley Bell Dings ]

07:34.087 --> 07:37.024
** [ Woman Singing
In Portuguese Continues ]

07:37.124 --> 07:39.059
[ Screams ]

07:46.299 --> 07:48.468
[ Tires Skid ]

07:48.569 --> 07:52.706
Oh, mon.
Lady, what planet you from?

07:52.806 --> 07:54.942
Brazil.

07:55.042 --> 07:56.977
[ Tires Screeching ]

08:11.124 --> 08:13.193
Hello.

08:13.293 --> 08:16.029
Hi.
I'm Isabella.

08:16.129 --> 08:18.498
Monica Jones
is expecting me.

08:18.599 --> 08:21.034
Ah, yes, of course.

08:21.134 --> 08:24.738
Unfortunately, Miss Monica
has been detained.

08:24.838 --> 08:27.140
Detained?
What do you mean
"detained"?

08:27.240 --> 08:30.210
Oh, nothing serious.
For her, I mean.

08:30.310 --> 08:34.815
She'll be back
in a couple days.
She's left you a key.

08:34.914 --> 08:36.817
Thank you.

08:36.917 --> 08:39.152
Have you known
Miss Monica long?

08:39.251 --> 08:41.188
Yes, since
we were children.
Oh.

08:41.288 --> 08:43.190
But she left.

08:43.289 --> 08:45.192
Bahia has never been
the same without her.

08:45.292 --> 08:47.494
I don't doubt it.
[ Chuckles ]

08:47.595 --> 08:49.897
[ Grunts ]

08:49.997 --> 08:52.833
I can't take elevators.
I walk.

08:52.933 --> 08:54.868
Oh.

09:00.974 --> 09:03.611
[ Mutters, Grunts ]

09:03.711 --> 09:05.613
Thank you.

09:05.713 --> 09:07.648
You're welcome.

09:36.276 --> 09:39.179
** [ People Singing,
Chanting ]

09:43.917 --> 09:46.854
** [ Singing, Chanting ]
** [ Drums Beating ]

09:50.724 --> 09:53.293
[ Man ] Yemanja,
goddess of the sea...

09:53.393 --> 09:56.129
who fills our nets
with fish every day,

09:56.229 --> 09:58.165
accept our offerings.

10:00.000 --> 10:01.935
[ Portuguese ]
[ Portuguese ]

10:08.208 --> 10:11.011
Have you see Isabella?

10:11.111 --> 10:14.181
No.
Not since last night.
Is something wrong?

10:14.281 --> 10:17.751
Serafina,
where is Isabella?

10:17.851 --> 10:21.621
[ Scolding In Portuguese ]
Go away!

10:21.722 --> 10:24.725
Hey, wait, wait, wait!

10:24.825 --> 10:26.727
You are the son
of a fisherman.

10:26.827 --> 10:28.996
You must make Yemanja
an offering.

10:29.096 --> 10:31.631
She always gives you
the best fish.
Come on.

10:31.732 --> 10:33.333
You can go to hell,
Yemanja!

10:34.902 --> 10:37.237
** [ Singing,
Chanting Stop ]

10:48.816 --> 10:52.753
** [ Man Singing
In Portuguese ]

11:29.222 --> 11:31.825
[ Raining ]

11:31.925 --> 11:33.994
Good morning.
Oh, good morning,
Miss Oliveira.

11:34.094 --> 11:36.129
Oh, may I get you
a taxi?

11:36.229 --> 11:38.131
I can't take taxis.

11:38.231 --> 11:41.034
Of course not.

11:46.373 --> 11:49.109
Sorry. He's no longer
the manager.

11:49.209 --> 11:51.244
Do you have any openings
in the kitchen?

11:52.980 --> 11:55.148
Washing dishes.

11:55.248 --> 11:58.418
No, I'm a chef.
[ Chuckles ]
Of course you are, my dear.

11:58.518 --> 12:00.888
And I'm Jeanne Moreau.

12:00.988 --> 12:03.023
I do wonderful
codfish bowls,

12:03.123 --> 12:06.226
and I am known for
my coconut-basted lobster...

12:06.326 --> 12:08.361
with passion fruit dip.
Do you do
fish and chips?

12:08.461 --> 12:10.363
Sorry?
Fish and chips.

12:10.463 --> 12:13.100
It's our most popular special.
Thursday nights.

12:13.200 --> 12:16.703
Yes, I can make fish and chips.
Maybe in a spicy batter with--

12:16.804 --> 12:19.239
Um, we are
fully staffed.

12:19.339 --> 12:23.076
Or plain batter.
Really fully staffed.

12:28.816 --> 12:32.519
[ Sighs ]
[ Thunder Rumbles ]

12:34.587 --> 12:36.489
Merda!

12:36.589 --> 12:39.159
** [ Man Singing
In Portuguese ]

12:39.259 --> 12:41.895
Shit!

12:48.501 --> 12:50.770
[ Speaking In French ]

12:51.839 --> 12:53.841
Monsieur Laroche?
Oui.

12:53.941 --> 12:56.509
I'm Isabella.
Isabella Oliveira.

12:56.609 --> 13:00.280
And?
I was the chef
at Yemanja.

13:00.380 --> 13:02.282
In Bahia. Remember?

13:02.382 --> 13:05.018
Oh, Brazil.
I remember.

13:05.118 --> 13:08.255
But you, I'm afraid--
You give me your card.

13:08.355 --> 13:11.524
You spoke of a possibility
of a teaching position.

13:11.624 --> 13:14.427
Oh, I can't really
hire novices.

13:14.527 --> 13:17.164
The spicy seafood soup?

13:17.264 --> 13:21.969
Oh, crustaceans
marooned in the most
exquisite fragrant broth,

13:22.870 --> 13:25.138
laced with fiery chilies.

13:25.238 --> 13:27.174
[ Sighs ]
Passion food.

13:27.274 --> 13:29.376
Food of the gods.

13:29.476 --> 13:33.780
But it's too late.
The semester
has already started.

13:33.881 --> 13:35.916
Perhaps next year, huh?

13:36.016 --> 13:38.418
- [ Woman Screams,
Dishes Break ]
- Hyperventilation.

13:38.518 --> 13:41.121
The soufflé fell... again.

13:41.221 --> 13:45.959
Oh, it's a class
for the publique générale,
two-week course.

13:46.960 --> 13:50.430
Uh, I'm sure you wouldn't
be interested. Are you?

13:52.299 --> 13:54.834
** [ Man Singing
In Portuguese ]

14:06.046 --> 14:08.615
What happened?
Where are the fish?

14:10.417 --> 14:13.553
You shouldn't curse
Yemanja.

14:23.696 --> 14:29.069
Good morning.
I am Isabella Oliveira,
and I am your new teacher.

14:29.169 --> 14:33.340
I come from
a place called Bahia,
in the northeast of Brazil.

14:33.440 --> 14:37.244
There we have
a very unique way
of cooking,

14:37.344 --> 14:40.213
so I will-- I will not
give you my recipes.

14:40.313 --> 14:43.183
I will show you
what inspires me,

14:43.283 --> 14:46.353
in the hope that you will find
your own inspiration. Okay?

14:46.453 --> 14:48.355
I think that to cook well,

14:48.455 --> 14:53.393
you must bring all your
feelings and experience
to the act of creation.

14:55.595 --> 14:59.266
Let's start...
with my passion--

14:59.366 --> 15:01.201
chili peppers.

15:01.301 --> 15:04.004
They come
from the Americas...

15:04.104 --> 15:07.607
and were found here
long before the arrival
of Columbus.

15:07.707 --> 15:11.411
Hold them in your hand.
Notice the colors.

15:11.511 --> 15:14.081
Now sniff.

15:14.181 --> 15:16.083
Okay, what do you smell?

15:16.183 --> 15:18.118
Can you describe
the sensation?

15:19.519 --> 15:21.588
How about you?

15:22.655 --> 15:26.059
[ Sniffs ]
Oh, I smell...

15:26.159 --> 15:29.562
a walk on a moonlit beach
in Acapulco.

15:29.662 --> 15:32.365
[ Chuckles ]
When did you become a poet?

15:32.465 --> 15:35.635
What do you expect me
to say, Esther?
It smells like a vegetable?

15:35.735 --> 15:37.637
[ All Laughing ]

15:37.737 --> 15:41.541
So, now here's my favorite--
malagueta pepper.

15:41.641 --> 15:44.011
Don't be fooled
by its tiny size.

15:44.111 --> 15:46.613
On the heat scale,
it is a very hot ten.

15:46.713 --> 15:50.650
But what I love most
about it is its smell,

15:50.750 --> 15:53.286
its aroma...

15:53.386 --> 15:55.955
and a flavor
you can never forget.

15:59.126 --> 16:03.230
** [ Bossa Nova ]

16:43.770 --> 16:45.705
So, when you work
with the chilies,

16:45.805 --> 16:50.343
remember to coat
your fingers with oil
so your skin won't burn.

16:53.346 --> 16:55.582
The smooth flavor
of a chili...

16:55.682 --> 16:59.018
is found
on the outside part.

16:59.119 --> 17:03.190
The part that burns
are the ribs and seeds.

17:03.290 --> 17:06.425
That's where the fire
comes from.

17:06.526 --> 17:09.762
[ Heart Beating ]

17:27.513 --> 17:29.449
- [ Knife Slices ]
- [ All Gasp ]

17:31.384 --> 17:33.220
I'm sorry.

17:34.421 --> 17:36.323
[ Isabella ]
I'll be fine.

17:36.423 --> 17:39.025
[ Murmuring ]
I'll be fine.

17:39.126 --> 17:41.428
** [ Woman Singing
In Portuguese ]

17:41.528 --> 17:44.564
[ Sobbing ]

18:13.493 --> 18:16.396
** [ Woman Continues
Singing In Portuguese ]

18:30.177 --> 18:33.346
[ Screams ]
[ Man On TV ] And now
we wrap tonight's broadcast...

18:33.446 --> 18:36.115
with thoughts from
best-selling author,
Claudia Hunter,

18:36.216 --> 18:40.753
whose new book
Women Who Love Men They Hate
has just hit the shelves.

18:42.589 --> 18:44.857
Women in love
with rotten guys.

18:44.957 --> 18:46.859
Are you one of them?

18:46.959 --> 18:50.129
Do you love someone who
emotionally jerks you around?

18:50.230 --> 18:54.367
Are you hooked on
a handsome, charming,
strutting peacock...

18:54.467 --> 18:59.672
who makes wonderful love,
but keeps you hidden away
in a small, dark kitchen?

19:00.607 --> 19:02.642
[ TV Off ]
Shut up!

19:16.989 --> 19:20.493
Go home!
Go home. Christ.

19:20.593 --> 19:22.895
We have no fish.
We have no customers.
We have no chef.

19:22.995 --> 19:25.432
Just help yourselves
to whatever's left
in the kitchen.

19:25.532 --> 19:27.434
Thanks, Mr. Toninho.

19:27.534 --> 19:30.537
Hey, come on, man.
Don't be like that.

19:32.905 --> 19:36.576
Ave Maria!
Look at the painting!

19:38.010 --> 19:41.714
All of our fish.
There they are.

19:46.519 --> 19:49.822
You're drunk.
Still, there they are.

19:52.259 --> 19:54.794
Toninho, the fishermen
are very angry.

19:54.894 --> 19:59.165
It's a sign. You must make
a formal apology to Yemanja.

19:59.266 --> 20:01.200
What she gives,
she takes back.

20:01.301 --> 20:03.202
You could lose
the restaurant.

20:03.303 --> 20:05.705
She didn't give me
the restaurant. I made it,
with my own hands.

20:05.805 --> 20:08.808
Every inch of it.

20:08.908 --> 20:11.844
This is my life.
This and Isabella.

20:11.944 --> 20:13.846
And no one is taking it
away from me!

20:13.946 --> 20:18.351
Toninho, what on Earth
possessed you to do
what you did?

20:18.451 --> 20:22.589
I mean, when a man
truly loves his wife,
he never lets her catch him.

20:22.689 --> 20:25.458
It's insensitive.
And not so smart.

20:25.558 --> 20:27.660
You are my friends.
Why are you making me
feel worse?

20:31.464 --> 20:34.367
I do miss Isabella's
coconut shrimp.

20:34.467 --> 20:39.238
[ Rafi ]
Oh, and her delicious
sweet "punhetinhas."

20:39.339 --> 20:42.842
[ Max ]
Oye, oye, oye.

20:52.852 --> 20:55.822
Yemanja,
bring her back to me.

20:55.922 --> 20:59.826
Gimme a sign, a clue,
a phone number.
Do something or I'll--

21:16.643 --> 21:18.578
Sign here.

21:29.889 --> 21:31.824
Hoo!

21:35.762 --> 21:38.264
[ Screams ]
[ Woman Screams ]

21:38.365 --> 21:40.266
Free at last,
free at last!
Monica!

21:40.367 --> 21:42.802
I missed you so much.
Thank Estée Lauder,
I'm free at last!

21:42.902 --> 21:44.804
[ Screams, Laughs ]

21:44.904 --> 21:47.540
She wasn't even pretty.
Are you sure?

21:47.640 --> 21:49.942
[ Laughs ]
I'm just playing.
Honey, he's a man.

21:50.042 --> 21:53.713
They're not like us--
faithful, romantic,
selective.

21:53.813 --> 21:56.849
They're like animals
on the Discovery Channel.
Fuck, fuck, fuck.

21:56.949 --> 22:00.587
That's disgusting.
I know.

22:00.687 --> 22:03.690
So, what did you do?
Why were you in jail?

22:03.790 --> 22:06.826
Nikos didn't tell you?
Remember Dominic?
No.

22:06.926 --> 22:09.696
He told me he wanted
a real woman that
could give him a family.

22:09.796 --> 22:13.933
So, in a fit of pique,
I doctored his good-bye drink
and muralized the dog.

22:14.033 --> 22:16.969
I used his body
as my canvas--
au Dominic.

22:17.069 --> 22:20.440
It's beautiful.
In Bahia, they would have
given you a medal.

22:20.540 --> 22:22.642
I can't believe
the son of a bitch
even pressed charges.

22:22.742 --> 22:24.644
[ Chuckles ]

22:24.744 --> 22:28.415
I missed you a lot.
You broke my heart
when you left Bahia.

22:28.515 --> 22:30.850
What about me, huh?
What about me?

22:30.950 --> 22:33.853
It's not my fault.
You're my best friend.

22:33.953 --> 22:36.456
You know,
"the retard twins."

22:36.556 --> 22:39.726
Little puking girl
and the boy in the dress.
[ Giggling ]

22:39.826 --> 22:43.563
But Daddy got called home
and it was "Bye-bye, Bahia."

22:43.663 --> 22:46.499
The diva had to learn
how to be all by herself.

22:47.834 --> 22:49.836
I've never been alone.

22:49.936 --> 22:52.338
One day I was a child
in my parents' home,

22:52.439 --> 22:54.974
the next
a wife in Toninho's.

22:55.074 --> 22:58.978
Well, now, girlfriend,
you are going to learn
to be on your own.

22:59.078 --> 23:02.482
But I'm so lonely,
I can't even cook...

23:02.582 --> 23:04.984
without thinking
of Toninho.

23:05.084 --> 23:07.454
Yesterday in class,
I smelled a malagueta...

23:07.554 --> 23:09.355
and nearly chopped
my finger off.

23:09.456 --> 23:12.124
Girlfriend,
if you love him that much,
why don't you forgive him...

23:12.224 --> 23:14.126
and go on back
to Bahia?

23:14.226 --> 23:17.697
To be locked in a kitchen,
while he flirts with
woman after woman?

23:17.797 --> 23:22.101
No! What I have
with Toninho is not love.
It's a curse.

23:22.201 --> 23:25.371
If I want to start a new life,
I have to get him
out of my head,

23:25.472 --> 23:28.140
out of my skin,
get him out of me!

23:28.240 --> 23:31.778
Okay. You serious
about this curse stuff?

23:32.845 --> 23:34.781
Yes.

23:36.983 --> 23:39.552
He's haunting me.

23:41.153 --> 23:44.123
Then, there's only
one thing we can do.

23:44.223 --> 23:47.827
[ Speaking In Portuguese ]

23:49.028 --> 23:51.097
[ Phone Ringing ]

23:53.633 --> 23:55.735
Isabella,
what took you so long?

23:55.835 --> 24:00.673
[ Woman Laughing ]

24:00.773 --> 24:03.543
Hello.
I can help you, child.

24:03.643 --> 24:07.547
But I warn you,
there's no looking back.

24:07.647 --> 24:10.016
Yemanja will take your love
to the bottom of the sea,

24:10.116 --> 24:12.585
and you will never love
Toninho again.

24:12.685 --> 24:14.587
Are you prepared for that?

24:14.687 --> 24:16.589
Are you prepared
for that?

24:17.924 --> 24:19.926
Yes.

24:25.898 --> 24:28.901
Okay. This is
what you must do.

24:29.001 --> 24:32.539
Find four fat
Mephistophelian crabs,

24:32.639 --> 24:34.841
the heart
of an artichoke,

24:34.941 --> 24:37.109
two ripe female mangoes,

24:37.209 --> 24:40.079
twelve drops
of midnight rain--

24:40.179 --> 24:42.782
Feather
of a black rooster.

24:42.882 --> 24:46.953
The eyes of two
boiled catfish. Uck!

24:48.821 --> 24:52.625
And finally,
sprinkle the ashes
of his burnt photograph.

24:52.725 --> 24:54.927
Allow me.

25:11.243 --> 25:16.115
[ Thunder Rumbling ]

25:23.623 --> 25:26.893
[ Thunderclap ]

25:26.993 --> 25:29.729
[ Thunderclap ]
[ All Gasp ]

25:43.142 --> 25:45.945
[ Thunderclap ]

26:17.076 --> 26:19.612
[ Birds Twittering
In Distance ]

27:28.247 --> 27:31.884
** [ Bossa Nova ]

27:42.261 --> 27:44.764
Okay, how about this?
"What's my orientation?"

27:44.864 --> 27:46.766
Every day,
we bring out guests,

27:46.866 --> 27:49.168
and a local celebrity panel
has to figure out if they're
gay or straight.

27:49.268 --> 27:51.771
[ Man On Phone ]
God, I wouldn't watch that.
Yeah, me neither.

27:51.871 --> 27:54.306
Oh, damn it, Cliff.
Just find me a 7:30 show...

27:54.406 --> 27:56.308
that won't get clobbered
by Xena.

27:56.408 --> 27:58.310
I know. I know.
I will find you something,
Alex. I promise.

27:58.410 --> 28:00.913
Just give me another day.
Yeah, well, you better.

28:01.013 --> 28:02.915
Thank you.
[ Hangs Up ]

28:03.015 --> 28:04.984
God, I hate my life.

28:06.886 --> 28:09.188
[ Sniffing ]

28:10.222 --> 28:12.124
Thank you.
Sure.

28:13.760 --> 28:16.195
Good morning.
[ Cliff ]
Wow!

28:16.295 --> 28:19.331
Thank you.

28:19.431 --> 28:22.034
** [ Bossa Nova ]

28:41.921 --> 28:44.857
** [ Man Singing
In Portuguese ]

28:56.568 --> 28:59.071
** [ Continues ]

29:23.395 --> 29:25.898
[ Indistinct Yelling ]

29:30.469 --> 29:33.372
Good-bye! Good-bye!
Sorry!

29:33.472 --> 29:37.376
Good morning.
I am Isabella Oliveira.
Welcome to my class.

29:37.476 --> 29:39.946
I see a lot of new faces
here today.

29:44.984 --> 29:48.287
** [ Man Singing
In Portuguese ]

29:48.387 --> 29:51.290
All right!
What, are you nuts?
You're crazy.

29:51.390 --> 29:53.525
My friend,
can you take me here?

29:53.625 --> 29:55.127
Oh, Christ!

29:56.628 --> 29:59.966
There's no address, mon.
Uh, I know.

30:00.066 --> 30:01.968
Will that be a problem?

30:05.504 --> 30:09.508
Now crush the garlic
in the mortar
with a pinch of salt.

30:09.608 --> 30:11.777
Measure with your senses.

30:11.878 --> 30:15.181
In time,
your fingers can develop
a tactile memory...

30:15.281 --> 30:17.216
for just
the right amount.

30:18.885 --> 30:22.554
[ Mashing Garlic ]

30:26.158 --> 30:28.327
Mon, you got to ring
more doorbells
than the Avon lady...

30:28.427 --> 30:31.297
you wanna find something
by this method.

30:31.397 --> 30:33.299
[ Sighs ]
[ Scoffs ]

30:33.399 --> 30:38.204
Sauté the bell peppers,
onions, tomatoes and chilies
in dende oil.

30:38.304 --> 30:40.940
Then, we add the stock.

30:41.040 --> 30:43.342
[ Sizzling ]
And when it comes
to a boil,

30:43.442 --> 30:45.344
add the shrimp.

30:45.444 --> 30:49.982
You will see that they are
ready when they turn pink
and begin to curve.

30:51.583 --> 30:54.253
Isn't that beautiful?

30:57.189 --> 31:00.592
To finish, pour into
a nice serving dish,

31:00.692 --> 31:03.462
and sprinkle
a little more cilantro.

31:05.064 --> 31:07.934
Thank you.
Sure.

31:09.201 --> 31:11.904
Voila!
Moquequa de Camarao.

31:13.572 --> 31:17.143
And remember,
the last and most
important ingredient...

31:17.243 --> 31:19.611
is to share it
with someone you love.

31:19.711 --> 31:24.283
I think it always improves
the flavor of the dish.

31:24.383 --> 31:26.885
That's all.
Thank you.
[ Applause ]

31:34.426 --> 31:36.328
[ Sips Loudly ]

31:36.428 --> 31:39.231
[ Gasping ]

31:39.331 --> 31:43.035
Too hot for you?
No.

31:43.135 --> 31:48.107
No. Um,
it's just new.
[ Hiccups ]

31:52.444 --> 31:55.014
Can I talk to you
for a sec?

31:55.114 --> 31:58.150
[ Woman On Phone ]
But if you call every
Monica Jones in the book,

31:58.250 --> 32:00.152
then your party must have
an unlisted number.

32:00.252 --> 32:03.889
But she's quite unique.
She's 5'10", braids,
great legs...

32:03.990 --> 32:05.891
and she's a man.

32:05.992 --> 32:09.261
In San Francisco,
that is not unique.

32:13.699 --> 32:16.602
You know, until two hours ago,
my entire definition of cooking
was, like,

32:16.702 --> 32:19.005
remove tinfoil
and nuke.

32:19.105 --> 32:21.007
I have never seen
anything like it.

32:21.107 --> 32:23.142
The whole room
was bedazzled by you.

32:23.242 --> 32:27.279
Where did you learn that?
I was a chef
in my husband's restaurant.

32:27.379 --> 32:30.082
[ Trolley Bell Dings ]
Ah.

32:30.182 --> 32:32.551
Is that too heavy?
No, it's fine.
Just fine.

32:32.651 --> 32:35.988
But, anyway,
I left him.

32:36.088 --> 32:37.990
Your husband?

32:38.090 --> 32:41.227
That's great!
I mean, why?

32:41.327 --> 32:43.929
Well, let's say
he was stifling me.

32:44.030 --> 32:46.432
Well, how could he?
How could anyone
stifle you?

32:46.532 --> 32:49.401
You are so, like,
like, the air.

32:49.501 --> 32:52.438
Like the-- Like the wind.
Like a fish.

32:52.538 --> 32:54.573
No, not like a fish.
[ Man ]
Please step inside?

32:54.673 --> 32:56.575
Would you come here?
I wanna tell you my idea.

32:56.675 --> 32:58.577
I can't.
It's okay.
Come on.

32:58.677 --> 33:00.579
I can't, really.
No pro--
Come on. It's okay.

33:00.679 --> 33:03.182
You'll be fine.
Whoa!

33:03.282 --> 33:05.184
Santo Deus.

33:05.284 --> 33:08.654
Are you all right?
I get motion sickness.

33:08.754 --> 33:12.158
Hey, hey, that's nothing.
When I get anxious,
I get the hiccups.

33:12.258 --> 33:14.160
[ Cell Phone Rings ]
Hold on.

33:14.260 --> 33:16.628
Yeah. Hey, Alex.
I did it.

33:16.728 --> 33:20.666
I got an idea.
We are coming right over.
You are going to love it.

33:20.766 --> 33:24.170
Okay.
What do you think?
A cooking show.

33:24.270 --> 33:27.439
Just like the class--
your recipes, your style.

33:27.539 --> 33:29.541
Everything
just the way
you want it.

33:29.641 --> 33:32.578
How does that
make you feel?

33:32.678 --> 33:34.680
[ Vomits ]
[ Man ]
You all right?

33:34.780 --> 33:38.384
A cooking show at 7:30,
for Christ's sake.
It's your wife again, sir.

33:38.484 --> 33:40.452
She says she's got
the travel agent on hold.
Why not?

33:40.552 --> 33:42.688
- Everybody's making dinner.
- No, they're not.

33:42.788 --> 33:46.125
Everybody's eating dinner.
Nobody wants to watch
a cooking show.

33:46.225 --> 33:48.627
Alex, just-- just--
just wait one second.

33:52.298 --> 33:55.701
Alex, this is
chef Isabella Oliveira.

33:57.403 --> 34:00.739
Isabella, this is
our station manager, Alex.

34:00.839 --> 34:04.042
[ Isabella ]
Hello.
Hi.

34:17.289 --> 34:19.056
A TV show!

34:19.158 --> 34:22.694
[ Screams ]
Holy Mary and Rhoda!
[ Coughs ]

34:22.793 --> 34:25.630
So, who's coughing?

34:25.731 --> 34:29.635
My producer.
Cliff Lloyd... Monica.

34:29.735 --> 34:33.371
Hi. Um--
[ Laughs ]

34:33.472 --> 34:35.474
That's-- It's quite
a nice place you got here,
Monica.

34:35.574 --> 34:38.244
It's very... artistic.

34:38.344 --> 34:41.045
[ Laughs ]
That's amazing how you
make that sound like an insult.

34:41.147 --> 34:43.047
[ Hiccups ]
Excuse me?

34:43.149 --> 34:45.317
I think
I'm making him nervous.
No, not at all.

34:45.417 --> 34:48.754
[ Hiccups ]
Um, so, Cliff, what's
the show gonna be like?

34:49.855 --> 34:53.625
Exactly as Isabella
wants it.

34:53.725 --> 34:55.726
How sweet.

34:55.827 --> 34:58.797
[ Man's Voice ]
You sure he's a producer?
[ Hiccups ]

34:58.897 --> 35:00.832
[ Hammering ]

35:04.870 --> 35:07.406
Excuse me?
Yeah?

35:07.506 --> 35:09.475
Why does everything
have to be so bright?

35:09.575 --> 35:14.079
- It's TV.
- I know it's TV.

35:14.180 --> 35:16.215
But how would it look
if we turned off these?

35:16.315 --> 35:18.217
And these and these.

35:18.317 --> 35:20.519
Uh, I don't know.
Give it a try.

35:24.856 --> 35:26.792
Looks good to me.

35:30.329 --> 35:32.531
And that's it for us
right now. Make sure
you stay tuned...

35:32.631 --> 35:35.634
for the premiere
of our new feature--
Passion Food Live.

35:35.734 --> 35:38.637
That's coming up next.
[ Woman ]
And we're out.

35:38.737 --> 35:40.872
Okay.
Thanks, everybody.
Great show.

35:40.972 --> 35:42.874
T-Tom,
are we going to dinner?
I've gotta go.

35:42.974 --> 35:44.876
I've got a tanning,
a massage, and you're
making me late for.

35:44.976 --> 35:47.112
I said we're over.
I told you last night,
"We are done."

35:47.213 --> 35:49.114
You are dumped!
I can't believe this!

35:49.215 --> 35:52.418
You have such
serious issues!
You are a blithering idiot.

35:52.518 --> 35:54.820
I am not
a blithering idiot.
I am a public author.

35:54.920 --> 35:57.556
[ Arguing Continues,
Indistinct ]

36:02.561 --> 36:05.163
Oh! She looks great.

36:05.264 --> 36:07.866
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.
Let's-- Let's just
keep moving here.

36:20.479 --> 36:24.650
Yemanja, I am preparing
your favorite dish tonight.

36:24.750 --> 36:26.785
Please don't let me down.

36:26.885 --> 36:31.156
Wow. I really gotta start
wearing my hair down.

36:31.257 --> 36:33.792
Okay. In five... four...

36:33.892 --> 36:36.662
three--

36:36.762 --> 36:40.832
Good evening.
I am Isabella Oliveira,
and this is Passion Food.

36:40.932 --> 36:44.703
In this show,
you will learn to transform
simple ingredients...

36:44.803 --> 36:50.276
into sensual, delicious dishes
that fire the blood
and satisfy the heart.

36:50.376 --> 36:52.511
My God.
The camera loves her.
It's like a miracle.

36:52.611 --> 36:54.713
And now, I would like
to introduce my assistant,

36:54.813 --> 36:56.848
Monica.

36:56.948 --> 36:58.850
Hi.

36:58.950 --> 37:01.753
What the hell is that?
[ Stammering ]
I don't know.

37:05.957 --> 37:09.027
** [ Bossa Nova ]

37:12.030 --> 37:13.932
Play "Seasons,"

37:14.032 --> 37:15.967
the breaker of hearts.

37:20.071 --> 37:22.708
** [ Begin ]

37:36.355 --> 37:39.858
[ Announcer Calling
Play-By-Play, Indistinct ]

37:39.958 --> 37:41.960
[ Chattering ]

37:43.662 --> 37:46.965
[ Patrons Complaining,
Indistinct ]

37:47.065 --> 37:49.701
This always happens.

37:49.801 --> 37:51.937
That's it.
Don't stop.

37:52.037 --> 37:57.476
It's good for your arms.
Coconut milk is the main
ingredient in Bahian cuisine.

37:57.576 --> 38:01.347
Hard to extract,
but worth every drop of sweat.

38:01.447 --> 38:05.984
So, now ladle some hot water
over it and squeeze.

38:08.420 --> 38:10.689
Squeeze.

38:10.789 --> 38:13.325
Squeeze.

38:18.797 --> 38:20.832
And now, we are going to
reduce the heat,

38:20.932 --> 38:24.770
to bring all the flavors
and the scent of the sea.

38:24.870 --> 38:28.607
While it simmers,
we are going to cut
the tomatoes in quarters.

38:28.707 --> 38:31.577
Make sure your tomatoes
are full and plump.

38:31.677 --> 38:35.381
She's a natural.
But they should be firm
as well. Ripe but firm.

38:36.782 --> 38:38.884
...French bread
in coconut milk.

38:38.984 --> 38:43.422
Break the crust
so that the milk
can penetrate its center.

38:44.856 --> 38:47.025
Uh, whiskey, please.
Comin' right up.

38:47.125 --> 38:50.295
Hey, man.

38:50.396 --> 38:53.899
- Work it with your fingers
till it's pulpy--
- Isabella!

38:53.999 --> 38:56.702
That's my wife!
That's my wife!
Get out of my way!

38:56.802 --> 39:00.406
Do you work her
with your fingers
until she's pulped?

39:02.808 --> 39:06.612
[ Isabella Continues,
Indistinct ]

39:06.712 --> 39:10.749
It'll taste even better
if you share it
with someone you love.

39:10.849 --> 39:14.720
[ Woman ]
And we're out.
[ Applause, Cheering ]

39:14.820 --> 39:17.122
** [ Woman Singing
In Portuguese ]

39:24.863 --> 39:28.634
Shh!
Ladies and gentlemen,
I would like to make a toast.

39:28.734 --> 39:32.904
To our cast and crew
for an unbelievably successful
first show.

39:33.004 --> 39:37.142
And, of course,
to Brazil's own gift to us,

39:38.109 --> 39:40.512
the extraordinary
Isabella!

39:40.612 --> 39:42.514
- [ Applause, Cheering ]
- Hear! Hear!

39:42.614 --> 39:44.616
Oh, whatever.
Bravo.

39:44.716 --> 39:46.618
** [ Continues ]

39:48.787 --> 39:50.956
You're gonna change
my life.

39:52.991 --> 39:55.060
Hey, taxi!
Stop! Stop!

39:55.160 --> 39:57.062
[ Tires Skid ]

39:57.162 --> 40:01.032
How could she?
Squeezing her coconuts
for all the world to see!

40:01.132 --> 40:03.535
Your girlfriend's
a stripper, mon?

40:03.635 --> 40:06.472
Mine too.
You get used to it.

40:07.639 --> 40:11.042
There she is!
Stop! Stop! Stop!

40:11.142 --> 40:13.712
[ Tires Skid,
Horn Honks ]

40:13.812 --> 40:15.847
Isabella!
[ Monica ]
Oh, my God!

40:15.947 --> 40:18.917
Toninho!
Yemanja be praised.

40:19.017 --> 40:21.620
I need to speak to you.
Alone.

40:21.720 --> 40:24.756
Uh, Izzy,
I'll be right here.

40:24.856 --> 40:26.858
What happened
to your face?

40:26.958 --> 40:28.627
What happened to my face?
I was defending your honor.

40:28.727 --> 40:29.961
That's what
happened to my face.

40:30.061 --> 40:32.130
My honor
doesn't need defending.

40:32.230 --> 40:36.167
Oh, no? I travel
half the planet searching for
the Isabella I know and love,

40:36.267 --> 40:38.870
and I find you on TV
looking so--

40:38.970 --> 40:41.573
You--
You're looking--

40:57.255 --> 41:00.025
Oh, you look beautiful.

41:00.125 --> 41:04.563
Like when we first met,
and I made you my wife.

41:04.663 --> 41:08.867
Your skin tasted of salt.
Your hair held
the scent of cinnamon.

41:08.967 --> 41:13.505
And when you kissed me,
your lips burned
with chili pepper.

41:14.840 --> 41:16.775
It made my head spin.

41:20.546 --> 41:22.848
Now, here you are.

41:22.948 --> 41:24.850
Come home with me,
where you belong.

41:24.950 --> 41:29.487
I belong
where I choose to be,
and I choose to be here.

41:30.722 --> 41:32.624
Do you also choose
to dress like this?

41:32.724 --> 41:34.860
It's inappropriate.
Not in your condition.

41:34.960 --> 41:37.896
And what condition
is that?
Married to me.

41:37.996 --> 41:40.465
Funny.
You don't act married.

41:40.566 --> 41:44.035
For three years,
I've been lying flat
on my back for you.

41:44.135 --> 41:46.171
For three years.
Not to mention
little things,

41:46.271 --> 41:48.607
like I never get to
drive anywhere.

41:48.707 --> 41:52.177
You know, I'm not something
that can be moved around
like a puppet.

41:52.277 --> 41:55.080
Fine. From now on,
you can move wherever you like.

41:56.948 --> 41:59.685
Isabella, I swear
on my mother's grave,

41:59.785 --> 42:01.753
you are the only woman
I ever loved.

42:01.853 --> 42:05.490
Your mother
is still alive.

42:05.591 --> 42:08.860
That's not the point.
You can't leave me.

42:08.960 --> 42:11.663
You're my wife.

42:11.763 --> 42:13.699
Good-bye, Toninho.

42:15.000 --> 42:17.869
"On your mother's grave"?

42:17.969 --> 42:20.639
Honey, please.
[ Laughs ]

42:24.643 --> 42:27.646
Mon, this not
going to be so easy.

42:46.164 --> 42:48.066
[ Ringing ]

42:49.901 --> 42:52.337
Isabella?
Are you there?

42:55.173 --> 42:57.075
** [ Bossa Nova ]

43:05.083 --> 43:08.620
[ No Audible Dialogue ]

43:18.296 --> 43:20.866
[ Tires Screeching ]

43:28.940 --> 43:30.876
[ Laughing ]

43:36.948 --> 43:40.251
Madame Oliveira.
Alberto!

43:40.351 --> 43:42.988
You remember me?
Of course I do.

43:43.088 --> 43:44.990
Your show is the talk
of the town.

43:45.090 --> 43:48.226
It's an honor
to have you here
in my restaurant.

43:48.326 --> 43:51.262
But not in your kitchen.
Excuse me?

43:51.362 --> 43:55.133
Jeanne Moreau?
J-Jeanne Moreau?

43:55.233 --> 43:58.837
It will come back
to you.
Certainly, madame.

44:00.939 --> 44:02.774
Oh, mon Dieu!

44:02.874 --> 44:05.310
So, what was that
all about?
Nothing.

44:05.410 --> 44:08.046
I am being bad.
You bad?

44:08.146 --> 44:11.249
That's hard for me
to imagine.

44:11.349 --> 44:13.251
Oh.

44:13.351 --> 44:15.420
Thank you.

44:17.022 --> 44:19.925
You don't have to
buy me flowers.

44:20.025 --> 44:22.961
It's not a date...
is it?

44:23.061 --> 44:25.831
You thought it was
a business dinner?

44:25.931 --> 44:27.966
Yes.

44:28.066 --> 44:32.037
Oh... well... no.

44:32.137 --> 44:34.072
No?

44:36.141 --> 44:38.076
Oh.

44:41.980 --> 44:44.382
I'm sorry.

44:44.482 --> 44:48.386
I had a great time
with you, and you've been
wonderful to me,

44:48.486 --> 44:51.890
but...
I'm not ready yet.

44:55.126 --> 44:57.128
Someday, maybe?

44:59.030 --> 45:00.966
Someday.

45:05.136 --> 45:07.305
[ Isabella On TV,
Indistinct ]

45:07.405 --> 45:10.175
That much butter
could kill a guy.

45:11.442 --> 45:14.379
That much woman
could kill a guy.

45:19.417 --> 45:22.020
[ Isabella ]
So, take the banana slices,

45:22.120 --> 45:25.356
add some brown sugar
and let it melt.

45:25.456 --> 45:30.361
Then, a pinch of ground clove
and a generous amount
of cinnamon.

45:30.461 --> 45:35.233
Now, we add a dash
of cachaca, which will allow
the sauce to caramelize.

45:37.135 --> 45:39.037
[ Sizzling ]
And remember,

45:39.137 --> 45:41.306
you are to cook
with your eyes and nose.

45:41.406 --> 45:44.042
God, who the hell
is he? And who are
those men with guitars?

45:44.142 --> 45:46.477
This way, you will learn
to trust your senses.

45:46.577 --> 45:49.114
** [ Singing
In Portuguese ]

45:55.486 --> 45:58.924
Cut!
No. No, no, no.
Let it roll.

45:59.024 --> 46:01.759
Somebody get me
some aspirin now.

46:06.164 --> 46:08.466
[ Man ]
Hey, it's that guy.

46:08.566 --> 46:12.070
- Oh, my God.
- Did they rehearse this?

46:12.170 --> 46:14.105
Wait, wait, wait, wait!
You want him
to keep singing?

46:14.205 --> 46:16.274
Yes! Yes!
Just go out there
and hover.

46:16.374 --> 46:18.309
Keep it moving.
Keep it rolling.

46:24.582 --> 46:28.854
Okay. Now we are going to
transfer the bananas
onto our dessert plate.

46:28.954 --> 46:32.924
** [ Continues ]
Put the skillet
back on the fire.

46:34.893 --> 46:38.196
And add a little bit
of water to the glazing.
[ Groans ]

46:42.033 --> 46:44.936
It's a spicy,
fragrant dish...

46:45.036 --> 46:47.205
that I'm sure
you will enjoy.

46:48.907 --> 46:50.808
Thank you.

46:50.909 --> 46:53.578
All right.
Just wait one second.

46:58.049 --> 47:00.886
- And we're out.
- Are you out of your mind?

47:00.986 --> 47:02.888
Of course
I'm out of my mind.
You're avoiding me!

47:02.988 --> 47:06.057
Ignoring me.
You're not giving me
the slightest chance...

47:06.157 --> 47:08.159
to make it up to you,
and that's not like you,
Isabella.

47:08.259 --> 47:11.062
- I'm your husband!
- This is the husband.

47:11.162 --> 47:15.066
- He's cute.
- [ Groans ]

47:15.166 --> 47:17.936
Take him. Take him.
Take him. Come on.
This way.

47:18.036 --> 47:20.071
Take him. Good-bye.
Whoo! You're outta here.

47:20.171 --> 47:23.942
- [ Grunting ]
- Settle down!

47:24.042 --> 47:27.112
You can't arrest a man
for talking to his own wife.

47:27.212 --> 47:29.881
Since when did singing
become a crime?

47:29.981 --> 47:32.350
[ Door Slams Shut ]

47:32.450 --> 47:36.421
** [ Bossa Nova ]

47:36.521 --> 47:39.057
** [ Singing
In Portuguese ]

47:48.934 --> 47:51.102
Fantastic.
We gotta get ahold
of this guy. Read this.

47:51.202 --> 47:54.105
Okay. Um, "Isabella's
bold, sensual dishes...

47:54.205 --> 47:56.107
"bubble to the pulse
of their guitars.

47:56.207 --> 47:58.876
- Oh, I can see it now.
- "A feast for the palate,

47:58.977 --> 48:01.012
and now a feast
for a girl's eyes too."

48:01.112 --> 48:03.048
Good, huh?
Uh, "Bolder than
Julia Child,

48:03.148 --> 48:05.116
butcher than Ed McMahon"?

48:05.216 --> 48:08.353
- Well, that's for Monica,
but what can I say?
- So?

48:08.453 --> 48:10.989
So, I want you to get
Toninho and the troubadours
back on the set tonight.

48:11.089 --> 48:13.258
[ Stammering ]
Isabella hates him!

48:13.358 --> 48:16.261
Oh, you think so.
I know-- I know so.
She told me.

48:16.361 --> 48:18.263
And you believe her?
Yes, I believe her.

48:18.363 --> 48:20.431
Look, Cliff.
I'm not blind.
You like Isabella.

48:20.531 --> 48:23.868
That's fine.
But we happen to be doing
a cooking show here.

48:23.969 --> 48:25.971
And this Toninho kid
is the missing ingredient.

48:26.071 --> 48:28.906
He may not be good
for Isabella, but he's gonna
be perfect for the ratings!

48:29.007 --> 48:32.543
I'm telling you, Alex.
Isabella will never
agree to it.

48:32.643 --> 48:35.046
Well, that's why
you're a producer.

48:39.017 --> 48:41.552
No, okay? No!
I won't do it!

48:41.652 --> 48:44.889
It's too much.
The public loves him.
What can I do?

48:44.990 --> 48:47.558
Okay, the public loves him.
Then, he can have his own show.

48:47.658 --> 48:50.895
But not with me.
Look. I don' like it
and you don't like it...

48:50.996 --> 48:54.432
and Monica doesn't like it,
but the truth of the matter is
that the two of you together--

48:54.532 --> 48:58.903
Well, on screen, I mean,
have a certain chemistry...

48:59.004 --> 49:01.472
that the public...
adores.

49:01.572 --> 49:04.575
And the ratings
are going up so fast.

49:06.277 --> 49:09.580
[ Sighs ]
And the bottom line is...

49:09.680 --> 49:14.185
if Toninho's not on the show,
Alex said he will either
cancel the show...

49:14.285 --> 49:16.554
or replace you.

49:29.267 --> 49:32.603
You know...
I think you're right.

49:32.703 --> 49:35.306
[ Chuckles ]

49:35.406 --> 49:37.442
Let's see what happens.

49:37.542 --> 49:39.577
Great. I knew
you'd understand.

49:39.677 --> 49:42.580
Mmm. Thank you.
Great.

49:44.182 --> 49:46.517
I'm just waiting for
the other shoe to drop.

49:46.617 --> 49:49.154
** [ Bossa Nova ]

49:52.057 --> 49:54.359
** [ Singing
In Portuguese ]

50:10.175 --> 50:13.744
Hey, Tito Puente!
You're outta here.
Thank God.

50:13.844 --> 50:17.682
Hello. I'm Cliff Lloyd.
I'm here to take you
to the station.

50:17.782 --> 50:20.418
You're being offered a position
on Isabella's show.

50:20.518 --> 50:22.520
I knew
she would send for me.

50:22.620 --> 50:26.224
Yeah, well, she didn't.
The station manager did.
He's the one who wants you.

50:26.324 --> 50:30.528
She doesn't.
My friend, you have a lot
to learn about women.

50:37.135 --> 50:39.704
Monica,
what am I supposed to do
about this Toninho guy?

50:39.804 --> 50:42.006
Oh, my God.
I'm-- I'm sorry.

50:42.107 --> 50:45.009
What's the matter, honey?
Ain't you never seen a girl
in her altogether...

50:45.110 --> 50:47.545
not all together before?
N-N-No.

50:47.645 --> 50:50.415
I mean, yeah.
Okay. Stop.

50:50.515 --> 50:53.084
So, you got it bad
for Isabella, huh?

50:53.184 --> 50:56.621
Yeah, I guess I do.
I mean, what does she
see in this guy?

50:56.721 --> 50:59.624
You know, aside from the fact
that he is gorgeous,

50:59.724 --> 51:02.127
charming and sings
like an angel--

51:03.194 --> 51:05.163
Whoo! Mmm!

51:05.263 --> 51:08.499
No, honey, I am just kidding.

51:08.599 --> 51:10.568
So, this is none
of my business--

51:10.668 --> 51:12.537
which, of course, makes me
much more interested--

51:12.637 --> 51:15.640
but if you're thinking
about making a move
on Isabella,

51:15.740 --> 51:18.143
you might wanna learn
a thing or two
about Brazilian women.

51:18.243 --> 51:20.345
Like what?

51:21.512 --> 51:24.682
Let me see your watch.
Okay.

51:25.916 --> 51:28.286
Thanks.

51:28.386 --> 51:31.589
Tag Heuer. Whoo!
Yeah.

51:31.689 --> 51:35.426
What the hell!
If you wanna learn
about Isabella, honey,

51:35.526 --> 51:37.562
you have to learn
about Brazil.

51:37.662 --> 51:40.465
That's a $1,000 watch.
Now, Brazil
is more than a country.

51:40.565 --> 51:43.434
See, Brazil--
it's a sensation.

51:43.534 --> 51:45.436
It's a mood
you can't describe.

51:45.536 --> 51:47.572
You can't define it.
You can only feel it.

51:47.672 --> 51:49.840
Okay. Try. Try.

51:49.940 --> 51:53.844
It's, uh,
it starts in the South,
in Porto Alegre, see?

51:53.944 --> 51:58.649
Uh-huh.
And it makes its way
up to Recife, right?

51:58.749 --> 52:00.651
It's the drums
of Candomble.

52:00.751 --> 52:03.688
It's the, the samba
of Carnaval...

52:03.788 --> 52:06.791
and the tom-toms
of the Yoruba.

52:06.891 --> 52:10.228
You know, you feel it
in the soles of your feet,
up to your knees.

52:10.328 --> 52:13.198
to your-- all the way
to your heart.
Oh!

52:13.298 --> 52:16.267
You forget the watch,
okay?

52:16.367 --> 52:20.605
You have the moon.
You have the tide.
You have the stars.

52:20.705 --> 52:22.840
Isabella is Brazil,

52:22.940 --> 52:26.877
and Brazil is Isabella.

52:26.977 --> 52:29.347
And if you want her,
don't try.

52:29.447 --> 52:32.583
Don't plan or prepare.

52:32.683 --> 52:34.585
Feel.

52:36.887 --> 52:38.823
Feel.

52:42.593 --> 52:44.895
Whoo!
Whoo!

52:44.995 --> 52:49.133
[ Whistle Blowing ]

52:49.234 --> 52:51.869
** [ Bossa Nova ]
Melons are like boyfriends.
Shall I tell you why?

52:51.969 --> 52:55.473
To get a single good one,
you must 100 try.

52:55.573 --> 52:58.509
But why try more
than you have to?

52:58.609 --> 53:00.878
Hello.
I am Isabella Oliveira.

53:00.978 --> 53:04.181
And welcome to
a special edition
of Passion Food.

53:04.282 --> 53:08.386
Today, we'll be creating
a symphony of fruits
from around the world.

53:08.486 --> 53:10.421
We'll be right back.

53:10.521 --> 53:13.358
Cut!
Excellent, Isabella.
Two minutes, guys.

53:13.458 --> 53:15.360
How does she do that?

53:15.460 --> 53:17.862
Don't try to understand it.
Just feel it.

53:22.667 --> 53:25.270
I'm so happy to see you.
You look radiant today.

53:25.370 --> 53:27.605
Thank you.

53:29.374 --> 53:31.609
You know, there is something
we need to talk about.

53:33.444 --> 53:35.346
What are you doing?

53:35.446 --> 53:37.348
I can't help it.

53:39.450 --> 53:42.720
Can you please
stop sniffing my hair?
Gimme a kiss.

53:42.820 --> 53:44.889
No.

53:44.989 --> 53:48.526
Just one.

53:48.626 --> 53:50.528
You know...

53:50.628 --> 53:52.530
I think we should
get a divorce.

53:52.630 --> 53:54.532
Hmm?

53:54.632 --> 53:57.902
A what?
A divorce?

53:58.002 --> 54:00.471
There goes
the other shoe.

54:00.571 --> 54:02.807
What the hell
is going on?
I don't know.

54:02.907 --> 54:05.443
Okay, everybody.
Five seconds.
We're out of commercial.

54:05.543 --> 54:08.413
** [ Bossa Nova ]
In three, two...

54:08.513 --> 54:10.281
[ Mouthing Words ]

54:10.381 --> 54:12.750
When it comes to melons,
here is a tip.

54:12.850 --> 54:14.885
Wh-Wh-Wh-Why
isn't he singing?

54:14.985 --> 54:16.887
Don't ask, just feel.

54:16.987 --> 54:19.657
I will never give you
a divorce. Never!

54:19.757 --> 54:22.327
- You're my wife,
and I love you!
- Pull it! Pull it now!

54:22.427 --> 54:26.230
- Pull it now.
- Listen to me!

54:26.331 --> 54:27.998
Wings. Jeopardy!
Mad About You.

54:28.098 --> 54:30.868
[ Cliff ] Small World.
Infomercials Just get it!

54:30.968 --> 54:33.338
- Oh, my God!
- Whatever, just pull it!

54:34.605 --> 54:36.607
- [ Cliff ] You moron!
- What?

54:36.707 --> 54:38.843
I'm gonna take you--
Oh, man!

54:38.943 --> 54:43.814
You little Latin mambo mouth!
Do you know what
you've just done?

54:43.914 --> 54:47.952
This is live television.
Good. Then, everyone will know
how much I love her,

54:48.052 --> 54:51.255
you butt-licking,
television slave!

54:51.356 --> 54:53.358
Take that...
and that!
Aah! Aah!

54:53.458 --> 54:56.293
Cavemen! Cavemen!

54:59.897 --> 55:05.002
Shh. You naughty girl,
I hardly recognize you.

55:05.102 --> 55:08.573
I hardly recognize
myself.

55:08.673 --> 55:10.875
No, Cliff, you're not fired.
Not yet.

55:10.975 --> 55:12.810
We're gonna be
on the 11:00 news.

55:12.910 --> 55:14.945
"Real-life romance
on hot, new cooking show."

55:15.045 --> 55:16.947
[ Laughs ]
See ya.

55:19.384 --> 55:21.686
What am I doing wrong?
Is it because I love her
too much?

55:21.786 --> 55:23.688
If you love her so much,
why are you parking...

55:23.788 --> 55:25.690
the welcome wagon
at the neighbor's?

55:25.790 --> 55:28.426
Oh, you wouldn't understand.
You're not a man.
Toninho.

55:28.526 --> 55:32.296
Honey, that's probably
the nicest thing
you ever said to me.

55:32.397 --> 55:36.434
I can't believe that
she's punishing me so hard
'cause of one stupid mistake.

55:36.534 --> 55:38.436
One stupid mistake, honey?

55:38.536 --> 55:40.438
You've been smothering her
from the beginning.

55:40.538 --> 55:43.508
Stashed away in the back
of that restaurant.
She was the cook!

55:43.608 --> 55:48.446
The cook? Okay.
Father help us, okay?
[ Inhales Deeply ]

55:48.546 --> 55:52.583
Let's try the basics.
Why don't you try to be
her friend?

55:52.683 --> 55:55.786
Her friend?
Now trust me.
I watch a lot of Oprah.

55:55.886 --> 55:57.988
Friendship is the basis
of any good relationship.

55:58.088 --> 55:59.990
A relationship?
We didn't have
a relationship.

56:00.090 --> 56:02.059
We were in love!

56:02.159 --> 56:04.061
Like Romeo and Juliet.
Yes.

56:04.161 --> 56:06.063
Or Tristan and Isolde?
Yes!

56:06.163 --> 56:08.466
Sonny and Cher!
They all ended up dead.
Yes!

56:08.566 --> 56:11.001
Dead,
but in love.
Except for Cher.

56:11.101 --> 56:15.840
Toninho, you are...
a macho, romantic...

56:15.940 --> 56:17.842
primitive heterosexual.

56:17.942 --> 56:19.777
Honey,
that's so 20th century.

56:19.877 --> 56:23.047
Look. Step into
the present, okay?

56:23.147 --> 56:25.716
Look at Cliff.
Now he knows how
to be her friend.

56:25.816 --> 56:28.352
And I think
she's responding too.

56:28.453 --> 56:30.354
Cliff?
Yes.

56:30.455 --> 56:33.924
What could she possibly
see in that clown?
Oh, I don't know.

56:34.024 --> 56:38.496
Apart from the fact
that he's sweet and modern
and sensitive--

56:39.730 --> 56:41.966
Whock it out!
Steel!

56:42.066 --> 56:45.636
I'm just kidding.
[ Laughs ]

56:47.137 --> 56:49.039
[ Door Closes ]

56:54.144 --> 56:56.914
What are you doing here?

56:57.014 --> 56:59.584
I thought I could help you
at the market.

56:59.684 --> 57:02.520
Like I used to.
Remember? May I?

57:02.620 --> 57:05.790
No. Thank you.
Mm. All right.

57:07.191 --> 57:09.093
Maybe I could do the shopping
for you every day.

57:09.193 --> 57:11.762
This way, you won't have to
wake up so early.

57:11.862 --> 57:14.932
Toninho,
why are you doing this?

57:15.032 --> 57:18.135
Because I wanna be
your friend.
My friend?

57:18.235 --> 57:20.137
Yes.

57:20.237 --> 57:22.473
So, you mean if I have
a problem with a lover,

57:22.573 --> 57:25.610
can I come to you
for advice?
You have a lover?

57:25.710 --> 57:27.612
Not yet.
[ Sighs ]

57:29.714 --> 57:31.649
Do you think you can love
someone else?

57:31.749 --> 57:33.651
Yes.
No!

57:33.751 --> 57:35.820
For each person,
there is only
one perfect mate.

57:35.920 --> 57:38.689
The moment we met,
I knew it was you,

57:38.789 --> 57:41.125
and you knew it was me.

57:41.225 --> 57:44.529
So, if we give up now,
you can never love
this way again.

57:44.629 --> 57:46.531
Who gave up--
me or you?

57:47.632 --> 57:49.534
I didn't give up.

57:49.634 --> 57:51.936
I made a mistake,
and I regret it.

57:55.773 --> 57:58.809
Please, Isabella.
Give me another chance.

58:00.811 --> 58:02.947
I-I can't live
without you.

58:03.047 --> 58:06.083
I'll do anything
you want.

58:06.183 --> 58:09.720
Toninho,
don't make it harder.

58:09.820 --> 58:11.789
We can be friends.

58:16.160 --> 58:20.030
But I just don't...
love you anymore.

58:21.932 --> 58:23.868
I'm sorry.

58:33.210 --> 58:35.613
[ Rafi ]
Listen to me.
You gotta come back.

58:35.713 --> 58:38.115
There are still no fish
in the sea.

58:38.215 --> 58:40.951
And the fishermen are...
desperate.

58:41.051 --> 58:42.953
You're gonna lose
this restaurant.

58:43.053 --> 58:46.691
Sorry, Rafi.
I can't come home
without Isabella.

58:46.791 --> 58:48.693
Give everyone
their severance.

58:48.793 --> 58:51.862
Beyond that,
I can't say.

58:51.962 --> 58:54.264
** [ Man Singing
In Portuguese ]

59:00.270 --> 59:03.040
[ Cliff ]
You're becoming a star,
Isabella.

59:03.140 --> 59:06.210
Doesn't that
make you happy?

59:08.178 --> 59:10.815
I guess.

59:14.018 --> 59:16.253
Look. I did everything
I could to get Toninho
off the show.

59:16.353 --> 59:19.056
They just--
It's okay.

59:19.156 --> 59:21.091
It doesn't matter
anymore.

59:22.292 --> 59:24.294
** [ Continues ]

59:32.369 --> 59:34.905
** [ Bossa Nova ]

59:40.377 --> 59:42.913
** [ Singing
In Portuguese ]

59:51.188 --> 59:53.691
[ No Audible Dialogue ]
** [ Continues ]

01:00:22.086 --> 01:00:24.621
[ No Audible Dialogue ]
** [ Continues ]

01:00:31.696 --> 01:00:34.231
The last and most important
ingredient...

01:00:34.331 --> 01:00:36.867
is to share it
with someone you love.

01:00:36.967 --> 01:00:39.904
** [ Continues ]
Thank you.

01:00:41.105 --> 01:00:43.640
** [ Continues ]

01:00:56.754 --> 01:00:58.655
** [ Fades ]

01:01:04.962 --> 01:01:09.133
Hey.
What's up with you?

01:01:09.233 --> 01:01:11.201
I don't know.

01:01:11.301 --> 01:01:13.904
Everything was going
so well.

01:01:14.004 --> 01:01:16.673
And I feel as if the wind
is blowing right through me.

01:01:16.774 --> 01:01:20.244
Oh, baby.
What you feel is lonely.

01:01:20.344 --> 01:01:23.380
Sweetheart, you need
to fall in love again
and fast.

01:01:23.480 --> 01:01:27.251
Mm. I'm not in the mood
for love.

01:01:27.351 --> 01:01:29.186
Well, of course you're not.
You're out of practice.

01:01:29.286 --> 01:01:34.859
It takes an effort.
Honey, if you don't eat,
you don't get hungry.

01:01:34.959 --> 01:01:37.261
[ Door Opens ]
Okay, hold on
to your peppers.

01:01:37.361 --> 01:01:39.263
You are not going to
believe this.

01:01:39.363 --> 01:01:43.801
The network just called.
They are flying in
some executives tomorrow.

01:01:43.901 --> 01:01:45.335
The show might be
going national.

01:01:45.435 --> 01:01:47.938
Whoo!
Yes!
[ Laughs ]

01:01:48.038 --> 01:01:49.940
We're going national!

01:01:50.040 --> 01:01:52.676
* We're going national
* Oh-a, oh-a

01:01:52.777 --> 01:01:54.945
* National *

01:01:55.045 --> 01:01:57.147
Hey, what's going on?

01:01:57.247 --> 01:02:00.217
Aren't you happy?
This was our dream.

01:02:00.317 --> 01:02:02.987
Well, I am happy.
I'm just tired.

01:02:03.087 --> 01:02:05.022
Oh.

01:02:08.793 --> 01:02:10.828
Will you take me out
tonight?

01:02:12.029 --> 01:02:14.464
Yeah! Sure.

01:02:14.564 --> 01:02:18.102
Great. We can--
We can work on some ideas
for the show.

01:02:18.202 --> 01:02:20.170
No, not for work,
for fun.

01:02:20.270 --> 01:02:22.172
Can it be just fun?

01:02:22.272 --> 01:02:25.109
Fun?

01:02:25.209 --> 01:02:27.144
I can do fun.

01:02:29.814 --> 01:02:31.515
Um--
[ Laughs ]

01:02:32.817 --> 01:02:34.518
[ Sighs ]

01:02:36.821 --> 01:02:38.755
[ Buzz ]
[ Grunts ]

01:02:45.129 --> 01:02:48.365
Wow.
You look beautiful.

01:02:48.465 --> 01:02:51.035
Whoa!

01:02:52.336 --> 01:02:54.271
[ Keys Hit Floor ]

01:02:58.042 --> 01:02:59.977
Isabella.

01:03:02.847 --> 01:03:05.015
[ Glass Breaks ]

01:03:05.115 --> 01:03:07.918
[ Phone Ringing ]

01:03:08.986 --> 01:03:10.921
[ Ring ]

01:03:14.124 --> 01:03:15.960
[ Ring ]

01:03:17.427 --> 01:03:19.329
[ Answering Machine ]
Hi. This is Isabella.

01:03:19.429 --> 01:03:23.133
Please leave a message
after the tone. Thank you.
[ Beep ]

01:03:23.233 --> 01:03:26.770
[ Toninho On Answering Machine]
Isabella? Are you there?

01:03:26.871 --> 01:03:30.040
Isabella, I know
you want me to go away,

01:03:30.140 --> 01:03:34.544
Should I turn that off?
and I've given you
every reason to.

01:03:34.644 --> 01:03:37.381
But I want you to know
that whatever you do,

01:03:37.481 --> 01:03:39.783
I will always love you.

01:03:39.884 --> 01:03:43.320
Anyway,
here's this for you.

01:03:46.290 --> 01:03:48.592
** [ Bossa Nova ]

01:03:53.030 --> 01:03:55.365
** [ Toninho Singing
In Portuguese ]

01:04:16.186 --> 01:04:17.554
[ Cliff Moans ]

01:04:17.654 --> 01:04:20.424
Wait!

01:04:21.591 --> 01:04:23.527
Oh!
Ow!

01:04:24.661 --> 01:04:27.064
I want to
fall in love again.

01:04:27.164 --> 01:04:29.466
** [ Toninho Continues ]

01:04:37.174 --> 01:04:38.875
[ Tape Rewinding ]

01:04:40.210 --> 01:04:43.213
Isabella.
Isabella, wait, wait.
What?

01:04:43.313 --> 01:04:46.583
Look. There's nothing
I would like more--

01:04:48.585 --> 01:04:51.288
Did I do something wrong?
No, no, no.

01:04:51.388 --> 01:04:56.260
I just--
Look. I think this guy
still has his hooks in you.

01:04:56.360 --> 01:04:58.262
That's not true.

01:04:58.362 --> 01:05:01.398
Isabella,
I really like you.

01:05:01.498 --> 01:05:04.368
I just think you need
some time to figure out
what you want.

01:05:06.203 --> 01:05:08.105
I'll be around.

01:05:15.212 --> 01:05:17.147
Good night.

01:05:20.717 --> 01:05:22.619
[ Door Closes ]

01:05:26.723 --> 01:05:29.226
Oh, it's anemic.
It's bloody anemic.

01:05:29.326 --> 01:05:31.495
Give me a darker bronze
there, will you?

01:05:33.230 --> 01:05:35.265
[ Photographer ]
Oh, Isabella, ducks.

01:05:35.365 --> 01:05:38.402
I'm going to need
a big Julia Roberts' smile
from you in about 15, okay?

01:05:48.212 --> 01:05:51.315
Much brighter, okay?
Bring it up a little more.
I wanna see her.

01:05:51.415 --> 01:05:54.251
Cliff.
Yeah.

01:05:54.351 --> 01:05:56.653
I'm not sure
about this dress.

01:05:56.753 --> 01:06:00.991
What are you talking about?
You look unbelievable.

01:06:01.091 --> 01:06:02.993
Look. It's just
for one show.

01:06:03.093 --> 01:06:07.397
The executives wanted
to see you in something
less... ethnic.

01:06:08.632 --> 01:06:10.534
Ethnic.

01:06:10.634 --> 01:06:12.602
Cliff.
Alex on line four.
Yeah.

01:06:12.702 --> 01:06:17.207
Okay. Look.
You look beautiful.

01:06:17.307 --> 01:06:19.676
Really. Okay.

01:06:26.050 --> 01:06:27.984
[ Sighs ]

01:06:38.128 --> 01:06:40.364
[ Photographer ]
Right. There we go.
Good.

01:06:54.811 --> 01:06:57.547
[ Waves Crashing ]

01:06:57.647 --> 01:07:01.151
** [ Bossa Nova ]

01:07:12.396 --> 01:07:14.698
** [ Man Singing
In Portuguese ]

01:07:33.317 --> 01:07:35.352
Yemanja,

01:07:35.452 --> 01:07:38.422
I offer you these pearls...

01:07:38.522 --> 01:07:41.658
so the fish will
come back to Bahia.

01:07:41.758 --> 01:07:44.161
But about Isabella--

01:07:44.261 --> 01:07:46.196
stay out of my business.

01:07:46.296 --> 01:07:50.134
This is her decision.
And mine.

01:07:50.234 --> 01:07:52.569
When human love
is strong enough,

01:07:52.669 --> 01:07:57.474
no god--
not even you, Yemanja--
can take it away.

01:07:59.309 --> 01:08:01.211
Yemanja be praised.

01:08:01.311 --> 01:08:03.213
** [ Continues ]

01:08:17.560 --> 01:08:20.397
[ Man ]
Yeah, that's good.
[ Man #2 ] Let's do it.

01:08:20.497 --> 01:08:23.332
Oh, Mother!
[ Chuckles ]

01:08:23.433 --> 01:08:25.469
Who dressed you?
Vanna White?

01:08:25.569 --> 01:08:28.537
The suits.
It looks very bad?

01:08:28.638 --> 01:08:32.542
Baby, nothing
looks bad on you.
You're beautiful.

01:08:32.642 --> 01:08:34.743
They better not
come near my wardrobe.

01:08:34.844 --> 01:08:38.615
Where is Toninho?
Toninho quit two hours ago.
Isn't that nice?

01:08:38.715 --> 01:08:42.152
Stand by, everyone!
He quit?

01:08:42.252 --> 01:08:45.354
Why?
I don't know.

01:08:45.455 --> 01:08:47.557
Maybe he went back
to his restaurant.

01:08:47.657 --> 01:08:50.227
There is no restaurant.
He lost it.

01:08:50.327 --> 01:08:52.862
No fish, no chef,
no Toninho,

01:08:52.962 --> 01:08:56.200
no restaurant.
[ Speaking Portuguese ]

01:08:56.300 --> 01:08:58.301
What?
Okay, one minute.

01:08:58.402 --> 01:09:00.470
[ Monica ] Okay, baby.
Snap out of it.
We got a show to do.

01:09:00.569 --> 01:09:02.506
Come on.

01:09:06.876 --> 01:09:09.513
What is this?
Tabasco.

01:09:09.613 --> 01:09:12.282
I don't use Tabasco.
This is Brazilian cooking.

01:09:12.381 --> 01:09:14.651
Can I have
my malaguetas?
Orders from the network.

01:09:14.751 --> 01:09:18.255
They said "malaguetas"
are too hard
for viewers to find.

01:09:18.354 --> 01:09:20.557
[ Woman ]
Thirty seconds!
Don't worry.

01:09:22.859 --> 01:09:24.761
What about the lights?

01:09:24.861 --> 01:09:27.264
Network wants it brighter.

01:09:28.598 --> 01:09:32.301
In five... four...
Stop!
[ Muttering ]

01:09:32.402 --> 01:09:34.804
[ Whispering,
Indistinct ]

01:09:37.241 --> 01:09:39.643
** [ Bossa Nova ]
Good evening.
I am Isabella Oliveira.

01:09:39.743 --> 01:09:42.145
[ Man ] Uh, Cliff,
the gentleman wanted
more close-ups on Isabella.

01:09:42.246 --> 01:09:44.481
Forget the mariachis.
And lose the freak.

01:09:44.581 --> 01:09:48.885
She's not a freak.
She-- He's really
very pleasant.

01:09:48.984 --> 01:09:52.421
Hey, hey.
Whatever you like, buddy,
but not on this show, okay?

01:09:52.522 --> 01:09:56.826
Today, we are going to
create a classic dish
from the north of Brazil--

01:09:56.926 --> 01:09:59.195
"Bobo de Camaraoes."
[ Man ]
Okay, move in.

01:09:59.296 --> 01:10:01.565
Stay-- Stay--
Have him stay tight
on her.

01:10:01.665 --> 01:10:05.435
Don't loose it.
Keep it nice and bright.

01:10:05.535 --> 01:10:08.438
[ Cliff ] Okay.
Think sexy. We're not that
interested in the food, okay?

01:10:08.538 --> 01:10:11.308
[ Laughing ]
Good. Great.

01:10:11.408 --> 01:10:14.177
Garnish it with farofa
and a sliced avocado.

01:10:14.278 --> 01:10:16.846
And be sure and enjoy it
with someone you love.

01:10:16.946 --> 01:10:20.650
Okay. Good job.
Let's go get her.
All right?

01:10:20.750 --> 01:10:22.686
[ Buzzer Buzzes ]

01:10:23.820 --> 01:10:25.722
It was terrific.
Brava!

01:10:25.822 --> 01:10:28.525
You are going to love
being a part of our family,
Isabella.

01:10:28.625 --> 01:10:32.462
We promise we have
big things in mind
for you, okay?

01:10:32.562 --> 01:10:36.600
It was great!
How can you go along
with this?

01:10:36.700 --> 01:10:38.602
Look. I know it's rough,
but they just have...

01:10:38.702 --> 01:10:42.439
a more streamlined vision
of the show because
it's going national,

01:10:42.539 --> 01:10:44.574
and everybody's excited.
Vision?

01:10:44.674 --> 01:10:46.576
I thought that was
my department.

01:10:46.676 --> 01:10:50.480
Of course it is,
but this is bigger
than us now.

01:10:50.580 --> 01:10:53.883
And look.
These guys love you,
Isabella.

01:10:53.983 --> 01:10:57.621
In fact, they love you so much,
they want you to be
the whole focus of the show.

01:10:57.721 --> 01:10:59.756
And what does that mean?

01:10:59.856 --> 01:11:03.760
[ Stammering ]
They think Monica might be
too much for the Midwest.

01:11:03.860 --> 01:11:05.795
I'm so sorry, Monica.

01:11:05.895 --> 01:11:09.499
These guys are businessmen.
You know, they can't sell drag
in Albuquerque.

01:11:09.599 --> 01:11:12.669
Cliff, I'm not going to
do the show without Monica.

01:11:12.769 --> 01:11:16.606
But you have to do the show.
I mean, this is your dream!

01:11:16.706 --> 01:11:18.908
This is not my dream.
This is your dream.

01:11:19.008 --> 01:11:21.945
For me,
this is a nightmare.
Isabella, please.

01:11:22.045 --> 01:11:25.915
You're a star now.
You belong to the world,
to your fans.

01:11:26.015 --> 01:11:28.452
This isn't really
your decision anymore.

01:11:28.552 --> 01:11:31.388
No?
No.

01:11:31.488 --> 01:11:34.524
You know what?

01:11:34.624 --> 01:11:36.526
I quit.

01:11:36.626 --> 01:11:38.528
[ Cheering ]

01:11:42.499 --> 01:11:46.870
That creep.
He turned out to be
just as bad as all the rest.

01:11:46.970 --> 01:11:49.305
Well, maybe that wasn't
Cliff's finest hour,

01:11:49.406 --> 01:11:52.942
but I'm sure he wasn't
trying to hurt anybody
on purpose.

01:11:53.042 --> 01:11:55.545
He's just a little confused.
Poor baby.

01:12:03.052 --> 01:12:04.888
Hey, Izzy.

01:12:04.988 --> 01:12:09.693
Let's go home
and get wasted.
Okay.

01:12:09.793 --> 01:12:11.961
** [ Guitar Playing Softly ]

01:12:18.802 --> 01:12:21.538
[ Toninho Yelling ]
Isabella!

01:12:21.638 --> 01:12:23.540
[ Groans ]
[ Groans ]

01:12:34.083 --> 01:12:35.985
[ Laughs ]

01:12:36.085 --> 01:12:40.824
Sweet bird of youth, girl.
Come see this. Come on.

01:12:43.059 --> 01:12:44.961
Isabella!

01:12:45.061 --> 01:12:48.865
I want you to lead
when we dance!

01:12:48.965 --> 01:12:51.100
I want you
to drive the car!

01:12:52.836 --> 01:12:54.738
I want you on top!

01:12:56.205 --> 01:12:58.608
I wouldn't want you
any other way!

01:12:58.708 --> 01:13:00.877
Oh, my God.
Can you hear me?

01:13:05.715 --> 01:13:08.017
** [ Singing In Portuguese ]

01:13:12.856 --> 01:13:15.592
Go on!
Go, go, go!

01:14:07.677 --> 01:14:10.614
** [ Instrumental Continues ]

01:14:40.109 --> 01:14:43.479
[ Thunder Rumbling ]

01:14:49.819 --> 01:14:52.121
Oh, boy.
Love versus voodoo.

01:15:06.670 --> 01:15:09.739
Why couldn't you have
been like this before?

01:15:09.839 --> 01:15:12.842
I don't know.
But I'm like this now.

01:15:12.942 --> 01:15:15.478
Now is too late.

01:15:15.579 --> 01:15:18.782
Kiss me,
then tell me that.

01:15:24.754 --> 01:15:26.656
[ Thunderclap ]

01:15:26.756 --> 01:15:30.159
[ Gasps ]
Ooh la la!
This looks bad.

01:15:48.678 --> 01:15:51.047
Isabella,
what happened to you?

01:16:03.960 --> 01:16:05.862
[ Sighs ]

01:16:07.296 --> 01:16:09.232
What have I done?

01:16:16.640 --> 01:16:18.608
Almost.

01:16:20.309 --> 01:16:22.245
Get it up.

01:16:27.651 --> 01:16:29.352
Let's go.

01:16:38.061 --> 01:16:41.698
[ Vomiting, Gasping ]

01:16:42.932 --> 01:16:44.834
You're cooking now?

01:16:44.934 --> 01:16:49.072
I have to make an offering
to Yemanja and ask her
to undo the spell.

01:16:49.172 --> 01:16:53.209
Isabella, Serafina told you
the spell is irreversible.
It won't work.

01:16:53.309 --> 01:16:57.213
It has to work.
She will understand
and give me back my love.

01:16:57.313 --> 01:16:59.849
But-- Oh!

01:17:01.250 --> 01:17:03.887
What's wrong with these
stupid eggs? Damn it!

01:17:09.058 --> 01:17:11.661
Monica!

01:17:11.761 --> 01:17:13.596
Monica!

01:17:13.697 --> 01:17:15.732
I've lost it.
Oh.

01:17:15.832 --> 01:17:18.101
Oh, girl, it's not
the prettiest thing
I ever seen.

01:17:18.201 --> 01:17:21.270
But, um, listen,
I'm sure it tastes--

01:17:21.370 --> 01:17:23.306
Try it.

01:17:25.108 --> 01:17:27.176
Mmm.
[ Gags ]

01:17:27.276 --> 01:17:29.779
I can't cook anymore.
Uh, no.

01:17:29.879 --> 01:17:33.282
Honey, everybody
has an off day.
It's fine.

01:17:33.382 --> 01:17:35.284
Look.
Everything is ruined!

01:17:35.384 --> 01:17:39.155
Okay. Listen.
Calm down, okay?
We'll fix it.

01:17:39.255 --> 01:17:44.093
We'll... use the soufflé
as a base, pretty it up
with this stuff.

01:17:44.193 --> 01:17:46.763
Girl, she'll never know
the difference.

01:17:46.863 --> 01:17:49.165
[ Thunder Rumbling ]

01:17:51.935 --> 01:17:54.337
Yemanja, please...

01:17:55.772 --> 01:17:57.974
don't reject my offering.

01:18:00.744 --> 01:18:02.445
Give me back my love.

01:19:31.034 --> 01:19:32.936
Merda.

01:19:44.613 --> 01:19:46.950
[ Toninho ]
Isabella.

01:19:49.953 --> 01:19:52.355
Toninho.

01:19:52.455 --> 01:19:55.291
How did you know
I was here?

01:19:55.391 --> 01:19:57.393
Monica told me.

01:19:57.493 --> 01:19:59.929
I came to say good-bye.

01:20:04.133 --> 01:20:06.169
I wish there was something
I could do.

01:20:06.269 --> 01:20:09.538
There is.
Why don't we cook
something before I go?

01:20:09.638 --> 01:20:13.009
For old times' sake.
I don't think
I can cook anymore.

01:20:13.109 --> 01:20:17.546
Neither can I.
But together,
maybe we can find a way.

01:20:17.646 --> 01:20:20.917
** [ Bossa Nova ]

01:20:33.662 --> 01:20:35.899
It's working.

01:20:40.904 --> 01:20:43.572
** [ Woman Vocalizing ]

01:21:43.232 --> 01:21:45.568
** [ Woman Singing
In Portuguese ]

01:22:23.539 --> 01:22:25.941
[ Thunderclap ]

01:22:45.228 --> 01:22:48.297
[ Thunderclap ]

01:22:55.404 --> 01:22:57.306
It's salty.

01:22:57.406 --> 01:22:59.308
It tastes like seawater.

01:23:15.491 --> 01:23:18.261
Toninho.
Yes.

01:23:21.230 --> 01:23:23.599
I love you.
You love me?

01:23:26.735 --> 01:23:28.671
Isabella.

01:23:37.846 --> 01:23:40.783
** [ Man And Woman ]
Singing In Portuguese ]

01:23:48.757 --> 01:23:53.296
[ Monica ]
Thus, ends our story
of Isabella and her Toninho.

01:23:54.763 --> 01:23:57.700
They lived
happily ever after.

01:23:57.800 --> 01:23:59.702
And so did we.

01:24:02.571 --> 01:24:04.473
Yemanja be praised.

01:24:04.573 --> 01:24:08.077
** [ Man And Woman
Singing In Portuguese ]

01:24:37.573 --> 01:24:39.542
** [ Continues ]

01:25:53.349 --> 01:25:55.651
** [ Up-tempo,
Bossa Nova ]

01:28:45.688 --> 01:28:47.590
** [ Slower Tempo ]

01:31:49.638 --> 01:31:51.540
** [ Ends ]
